<subSubSection id="4FFD6520FFB9FFEFD0ECFC777995FA17" pageId="7" pageNumber="30" type="description">
<paragraph id="075836ABFFB9FFEFD0ECFC777CBCFB7F" blockId="7.[151,1437,965,1567]" pageId="7" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis id="3593EAB9FFB9FFEFD0ECFC7779C7FBA7" bold="true" box="[199,463,1001,1027]" pageId="7" pageNumber="30">External morphology.</emphasis>
Body dark brown (
<figureCitation id="9FDC2A2EFFB9FFEFD299FC777B07FBA7" box="[690,783,1001,1027]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1888,1913]" captionTargetBox="[244,1345,184,1858]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[229,1359,174,1869]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. Balala curvata Shen &amp; Zhang, 1995, Holotype ♂: A. Habitus, ventral view; B. Habitus, lateral view; C. Head and pronotum, dorsal view; D. Exposed part of mesonotum and scutellum, dorsal view; E. Face; F. Pygofer, lateral view; G. Pygofer, dorsal view; H. Pygofer, ventral view; I. Subgenital plate, ventral view; J. Aedeagus, connective and style, lateral view; K. Connective and style, ventral view; L. Aedeagus, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3635588" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3635588/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="30">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
). Crown (
<figureCitation id="9FDC2A2EFFB9FFEFD3A8FC777BD3FBA7" box="[899,987,1001,1027]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1888,1913]" captionTargetBox="[244,1345,184,1858]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[229,1359,174,1869]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. Balala curvata Shen &amp; Zhang, 1995, Holotype ♂: A. Habitus, ventral view; B. Habitus, lateral view; C. Head and pronotum, dorsal view; D. Exposed part of mesonotum and scutellum, dorsal view; E. Face; F. Pygofer, lateral view; G. Pygofer, dorsal view; H. Pygofer, ventral view; I. Subgenital plate, ventral view; J. Aedeagus, connective and style, lateral view; K. Connective and style, ventral view; L. Aedeagus, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3635588" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3635588/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="30">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
) anterior margin slightly angulate with three triangularly arranged small tubercles at apex, length shorter than width between eyes. Exposed part of mesonotum and scutellum (
<figureCitation id="9FDC2A2EFFB9FFEFD18CFBAF7A20FBEF" box="[423,552,1073,1099]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1888,1913]" captionTargetBox="[244,1345,184,1858]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[229,1359,174,1869]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. Balala curvata Shen &amp; Zhang, 1995, Holotype ♂: A. Habitus, ventral view; B. Habitus, lateral view; C. Head and pronotum, dorsal view; D. Exposed part of mesonotum and scutellum, dorsal view; E. Face; F. Pygofer, lateral view; G. Pygofer, dorsal view; H. Pygofer, ventral view; I. Subgenital plate, ventral view; J. Aedeagus, connective and style, lateral view; K. Connective and style, ventral view; L. Aedeagus, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3635588" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3635588/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="30">Figs. 4B, D</figureCitation>
) truncated well short of clavus, exposed part of mesonotum about 1/5 as long as scutellum, scutellum with centre compressed into keel vertically and obliquely truncate subapically in lateral view, median longitudinal ridge moderately weak and extended over entire scutellum. Forewing with one light-colored band present between apical cells and appendix. Abdomen with pair of yellow patches on 5th tergite submedially. Hind femur with 6 macrosetae at apex, tibia with ca. 9, 11 setae in rows AD, PD, respectively.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="075836ABFFB9FFEFD0ECFB7B7995FA17" blockId="7.[151,1437,965,1567]" pageId="7" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis id="3593EAB9FFB9FFEFD0ECFB7B7970FB5B" bold="true" box="[199,376,1252,1279]" pageId="7" pageNumber="30">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer (
<figureCitation id="9FDC2A2EFFB9FFEFD1CEFB7B7A3AFB5B" box="[485,562,1253,1279]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1888,1913]" captionTargetBox="[244,1345,184,1858]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[229,1359,174,1869]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. Balala curvata Shen &amp; Zhang, 1995, Holotype ♂: A. Habitus, ventral view; B. Habitus, lateral view; C. Head and pronotum, dorsal view; D. Exposed part of mesonotum and scutellum, dorsal view; E. Face; F. Pygofer, lateral view; G. Pygofer, dorsal view; H. Pygofer, ventral view; I. Subgenital plate, ventral view; J. Aedeagus, connective and style, lateral view; K. Connective and style, ventral view; L. Aedeagus, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3635588" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3635588/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="30">Figs. 4</figureCitation>
F–I) with dorsal inner margin nearly straight, subapex of ventral margin a little angulate, many small short setae arranged along ventral margin; ventral appendage about half as long as pygofer, apical 2/5 sharply curved backward and tapering. Subgenital plate shorter than pygofer. Apical margin of connective (
<figureCitation id="9FDC2A2EFFB9FFEFD0B4FACF78E5FACF" box="[159,237,1361,1387]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1888,1913]" captionTargetBox="[244,1345,184,1858]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[229,1359,174,1869]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. Balala curvata Shen &amp; Zhang, 1995, Holotype ♂: A. Habitus, ventral view; B. Habitus, lateral view; C. Head and pronotum, dorsal view; D. Exposed part of mesonotum and scutellum, dorsal view; E. Face; F. Pygofer, lateral view; G. Pygofer, dorsal view; H. Pygofer, ventral view; I. Subgenital plate, ventral view; J. Aedeagus, connective and style, lateral view; K. Connective and style, ventral view; L. Aedeagus, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3635588" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3635588/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="30">Figs. 4</figureCitation>
J–L) nearly straight; style about 1.8x as long as connective, apical part reduced but beyond middle of connective; connective about twice as wide as long. Aedeagus tubular without teeth, preatrium about as long as shaft, gonopore at shaft apex.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
